Manual verification steps for AC #7 (runtime, two clients + mic):
1. Seed a voice channel (story 001) and start the server (npm run docker:up).
2. Launch two clients (npm run dev:client), register/login as two users.
3. Both call voice.join(voiceChannelId); grant mic permission in each.
4. Confirm audible two-way audio (each hears the other).
5. toggleMute() on client A → client B stops hearing A; unmute restores. Rapid toggles converge.
6. toggleDeafen() on A → A stops hearing B locally; peers see deafen flag.
7. leave() on A → mic indicator off, B receives voice.peer_left and drops A's audio; no dangling streams/transports.
8. Logout / 4001 auth-fail on B → voice tears down cleanly.

